text: Eureka is an unincorporated community in Walla Walla County, in the U.S. state of Washington. ==History== Eureka was laid out in 1904, and named after nearby Eureka Flat. A post office called Eureka was established in 1889, and remained in operation until 1964. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Walla Walla County, Washington Category:Unincorporated communities in Washington (state)
title: Eureka, Washington
